3.2, the agent which ships as part of
Leopard is an updated to support Leopard.

00:48:43.789 --> 00:48:46.670
And it also is included at part of Leopard.

00:48:46.670 --> 00:48:48.619
So if you have Tiger you have the two agents.

00:48:48.619 --> 00:48:50.940
Now you've got the three agent there.

00:48:50.940 --> 00:48:55.300
We've also spent some time working in
an adaptive codec as part of this agent.

00:48:55.300 --> 00:48:57.220
And the target here is DSL connections.

00:48:57.219 --> 00:48:59.969
We wanted to make it really, really good on DSL connections.

00:48:59.969 --> 00:49:04.779
The technology, which is part of ARD;
the same thing in iChat screen sharing,

