00:50:31.480 --> 00:50:36.380
But eager young minds found very easy ways to get around it.

00:50:36.380 --> 00:50:43.030
So what I'm happy to report is part of Leopard, we
have very robust application launch restrictions.

00:50:43.030 --> 00:50:49.330
What this is, is if you're using a managed desktop, we have
a requirement to not allow certain applications to be run.

00:50:49.329 --> 00:50:50.949
We now block at the kernel level.

00:50:50.949 --> 00:50:55.509
This is going to be really, really tricky.

00:50:55.510 --> 00:50:56.430
( Applause )

00:50:56.429 --> 00:50:57.839
>> To get around it.

00:50:57.840 --> 00:51:00.970
It's not a test or anything -- we did a good job.

00:51:00.969 --> 00:51:06.939
Trust me. We also have hierarchal
management as part of Manage Desktop.

00:51:06.940 --> 00:51:12.829
If you're using Manage Desktop you can set preferences as
part of a user, as part of a group, as part of computers.

00:51:12.829 --> 00:51:17.630
What we do now is you actually stack them
hierarchically so we can get really sophisticated

00:51:17.630 --> 00:51:20.480
about the different management
policies that you want to construct.

00:51:20.480 --> 00:51:22.420
So go crazy.

00:51:22.420 --> 00:51:27.550
We also now have as part of Manage Desktop, command
line tools to actually get information out --

00:51:27.550 --> 00:51:29.769
( Applause )

00:51:29.769 --> 00:51:31.590
>> -- you guys love the command line tools.

00:51:31.590 --> 00:51:36.289
Always a round of applause on that.

00:51:36.289 --> 00:51:36.789
That's awesome.

00:51:36.789 --> 00:51:38.059
So, yes, we've got that as well.

00:51:38.059 --> 00:51:41.590
And you can get all the information about
what's going on in mcx. As always,

00:51:41.590 --> 00:51:44.670
we're adding new high level plug-ins in the Manage Desktop.

00:51:44.670 --> 00:51:48.909
We now support -- by high level I mean new
plug-ins that you see in workgroup manager.

00:51:48.909 --> 00:51:54.869
We now support Time Machine, all the
Dashboard widgets, Front Row as well.

